Configure cluster settings like ingress and kubeconfig context

Usage:
  mcp-runtime cluster config [flags]

Flags:
      --context string            Kubernetes context to use
      --force-ingress-install     Force ingress install even if an ingress class already exists
  -h, --help                      help for config
      --ingress string            Ingress controller to install (traefik|none) (default "traefik")
      --ingress-manifest string   Manifest to apply when installing the ingress controller (default "config/ingress/overlays/prod")
      --kubeconfig string         Path to kubeconfig file (default: ~/.kube/config)
      --name string               Cluster name for cloud provider kubeconfig (default "mcp-runtime")
      --project string            Project ID (GKE, planned)
      --provider string           Cloud provider for kubeconfig (eks; aks/gke planned)
      --region string             Region for cloud provider kubeconfig (default "us-west-1")
      --resource-group string     Resource group (AKS, planned)
      --zone string               Zone (GKE, planned)
